From ''hail'', a variant of [[hale]] ‘health, safety’.

====Transitive verb====
'''to hail''' (''past tense and past participle'' '''hailed''')

#To greet.
#:''Hail Caesar''
#To praise enthusiastically.
#:''He was hailed as a hero.''
#To call out to loudly in order to gain the attention of
#:''hail a taxi''

